  "summary": "Main\nBy Jeffrey Landsberg\nThe most recently released nation-specific import data shows that in April China imported 17.8 million tons of coal from Indonesia. This is down from March by 2 million tons (-10%) and is down year-on-year by 3.2 million tons (-21%). Indonesia has not surprisingly remained China's primary source of coal imports.",
